The paper discusses the design of password management schemes with a focus on usability and security. The paper introduces quantitative usability and security models and discusses the assumptions underlying password management. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of empirical studies to validate the usability assumptions, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also discusses the use of the Chinese Remainder Theorem in the construction of the proposed scheme, which suggests that it may belong to the categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
